This is a simple Ruby script to batch encode all .WAV files in one folder to .MP3s. ID3 Tags are populated by using the following file naming convention: "Artist_Name_-_Song_Title.wav"

Dependencies:
* Lame

Path:
For quick usage from anywhere in you file system add the script to your path variable
Go to home directory
>cd
Edit .profile
>vim .profile
Add line
export PATH=/Users/youruser/pathto/rubyscript/MP3-Batch:$PATH
Restart Terminal 
